Reasoning: The paper deals with the study of networks and community detection algorithms, which are commonly studied in the fields of social informatics (cs.SI), system and network dynamics (cs.SD), data structures and algorithms (cs.DS), network and internet architecture (cs.NI), and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper specifically focuses on the identification of small, medium-sized, and large communities in large networks, which is a problem that is relevant to all of these sub-categories.
